THE Soweto derby is set to headline the semi- finals of the MTN 8. The two Soweto giants will lock horns in the next stage of the competition after they were pitted against each other in the draw that took place on Sunday. Bloemfontein Celtic, who knocked out Mamelodi Sundowns in the quarter-finals, will face SuperSport United. Kaizer Chiefs, under their new coach Gavin Hunt, overcame Maritzburg United 2-1 at FNB Stadium. Orlando Pirates on the other hand, beat Cape Town City 1-0 to book a spot. #MTN8 Semi-finals:@orlandopirates vs @KaizerChiefs@SuperSportFC vs @Bloem_Celtic    